Ex-BBNaija housemates Tacha and Mercy Ike have made up after they fell apart during the show in 2019. The duo kept feuding after the show up with non-stop altercations on social media. But they made up during a joint interview with socialite Toke Makinwa on her exclusive show Talk with Toke Makinwa. They agreed that their feud was long overdue and they were tired of being at loggerheads.   Mayorkun blames FG for Kaduna train attack     Sharon Ooja, Kate Henshaw attend Netflix party in SA     I don’t deny myself of good living at 65 – K1 d…   When asked how they felt about their reconciliation, teary Mercy Ike said: “I think people from Nigeria like people fighting themselves. Please people if you want to fight, go and fight yourselves”. Tacha responded: “We are tired of fighting.” The full interview is set to be streamed on her next interview scheduled billed for April 9 on DSTV